Quote: From a departmental trial of inoculated [sic] clover seed sown with and without fertiliser on a sunny face and a dark face, it has been found that fertiliser is necessary to enable a quick establishment of clover plants, particularly on the sunny face, though a reasonable strike on the unfertilised dark face was obtained.
